  "texts": [
    "c) A customized LLM-annotated explanation revision technique that allows LLM to teach customized knowledge by guiding the LLM to pinpoint and correct inaccuracies in the reasoning steps of small models.",
    "d) Extensive experiments demonstrate that the proposed framework can improve annotating efficiency.",
    "DistilBert (Sanh et al., 2019) achieves efficient distillation of the BERT transformer into a student model with minimal performance loss.",
    "Tinybert (Jiao et al., 2019) introduces a loss term for matching hidden states between teacher and student.",
    "Works like (Magister et al., 2022), Finetune-CoT (Ho et al., 2022), KNIFE (Chan et al., 2022), SCoTD (Li et al., 2023), and Distilling stepby-step (Hsieh et al., 2023) emphasize multi-task fine-tuning of student models using both CoT reasoning explanations and LLM-generated answers."
  ],
